# Python and Pandas  <a id="pp"></a>
## Kaggle
Kaggle is a top platform for data science competitions and learning, offering datasets and coding environments. On Kaggle, I use Python and Pandas for exploratory data analysis (EDA).\
![alt text][defkimg]\
[My Kaggle Profile][defkp]

**World Most Populated Cities**
- I compared ChatGPT's data analysis to my use of Pandas by asking six questions about the dataset, but the responses were mostly unhelpful or incorrect, with both the 3.5 and 4.0 versions giving misleading answers.
- Out of over 80 megacities globally, only 15 are in developed countries. Asia (including Oceania) offers the most choices, followed by Europe, with North America having the fewest. Tokyo and Osaka each have over 20 million residents, while the other 13 cities have fewer than 10 million.

Kaggle: [World Most Populated Cities][defk4]

**Canada vs Australia Immigration Data Analysis**
- This project analyzes Australian and Canadian immigration datasets using Pandas' plot function to guide EDA and reveal insights. Detailed findings on immigration trends are available via the below link.
- Pandas' plot function is easy to use and effective for analysis, while Seaborn offers better-looking charts with more customization. However, Python visualization libraries don't match the capabilities of specialized software like Tableau.

Kaggle: [Australia and Canada Immigration][defk3]

**Countries by Steel Production: 1967-2021: China's Rise to Global Dominance**
- China's steel production skyrocketed post-2000, boasting a remarkable 12% growth rate, solidifying its status as an industrial powerhouse.
- As we delve into Seaborn for analysis, brace yourself for its powerful graphing features, though tweaking parameters might feel like navigating a maze at times.

Kaggle: [Countries by Steel Production: 1967-2021][defk2]

**Diving into Sydney Suburbs Reviews**
- Exploring Kaggle's Sydney suburb dataset, I delved into Chinese communities, analyzing population, housing prices, and pinpointing top-value areas using Pandas' native plotting.
- Key findings suggest Carlingford, Campsie, and Hurstville stand out as prime locations for Chinese-centric living, while nuances in perceptions and housing affordability surface, particularly in areas like Chatswood.

Kaggle: [Sydney Suburbs Reviews][defk1]

# Business Intelligence  <a id="bi"></a>
2023 Gartner® Magic Quadrant™ for BI and Analytics\
![alt text][defbigartnetimg]\
In the competitive field of Business Intelligence (BI), staying informed is key. Microsoft Power BI has emerged as a leader, surpassing Tableau according to the  Gartner Magic Quadrant report. Its success stems from value proposition and seamless integration with Microsoft Office products. Staying relevant means adapting to these changes and honing skills. I've worked extensively with both platforms, with a focus on Power BI, enriching my understanding of their intricacies.

# Data Storage and Integration  <a id="di"></a>
## Data Storage
2023 Gartner® Magic Quadrant™ for Cloud DBMS\
![alt text][defdatastorageimg]\
The data storage landscape is filled with many strong contenders, as highlighted by the Gartner report. Throughout my career, I've worked with Oracle and Microsoft SQL Server on-premises. With the industry's shift to the cloud, I've transitioned to using Azure SQL Database, Amazon Redshift, and Amazon S3. I have nearly 10 years of experience using SQL to interact with data across these platforms, allowing me to adeptly manage and manipulate data in various environments.

[Back to top](#top)

## Data Integration
2023 Gartner® Magic Quadrant™ for Data Integration Tools\
![alt text][defdataintegrationimg]\
I have a strong background in data integration, having worked as an engineer at institutions like the Ohio Department of Transportation and AT&T. My primary role involved providing ETL solutions, including data cleaning, loading, transformation, and delivery. This has honed my ability to manage and integrate data across various systems and platforms.

While many DBMS providers offer data integration capabilities, specialized tools like Informatica, Alteryx, and FME excel in integrating data from spreadsheets, on-premises databases, and cloud storage. These tools streamline the scheduling and management of data processes. Although Informatica's free community version is no longer available, my experience with these tools ensures efficient data integration in diverse environments.
### FME by Safe Software
![alt text][deffmeimg]\
I have over 10 years of experience using FME by Safe Software. Originally a geospatial tool, FME has evolved into a comprehensive ETL software. I've used it at three different organizations, developing over 100 data workflows to automate data pipelines and transformations. My work with FME includes advanced features such as scheduling, server management, and batch processing.

[FME by Safe Software Project Showcase](etl.md)
### Alteryx
![alt text][defalteryximg]\
While at Macquarie University, I used Alteryx, an ETL software with design and functionality similar to FME. In today's competitive market, many ETL tools adopt successful features from each other. I designed and maintained over 50 data workflows using Alteryx, enhancing data integration and automation.

[Alteryx Project Showcase](etl.md)

# Others  <a id="other"></a>
## Version Control with GitHub
![alt text][defgitimg]\
[My GitHub Profile][defgitp]\
I use GitHub for version control in both my work and personal projects. With more than two dozen repositories hosted, GitHub helps me manage and track changes effectively. Even this portfolio site is maintained using GitHub.
## Integrated Development Environment (IDE)
![alt text][defideimg]\
I have experience with various IDEs, having experimented with tools like Atom and Jupyter Lab in the past. However, I've found Microsoft Visual Studio Code to be the most effective and versatile IDE available. Its lightweight nature, user-friendly interface, and support for multiple programming languages make it stand out. Particularly for my work involving numerous Jupyter notebooks, Visual Studio Code's seamless integration proves invaluable. I highly recommend it for developers of all levels.
